oakcurric:unit-2939
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My personal world: Wer sind wir?"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-wer-sind-wir" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits the present tense of 'sein' and 'haben', weak verbs, open and
  closed question formation and word order 1 and 2. It introduces nationality nouns and
  gender neutral language, and reinforces simple (I do) and ongoing (I am doing) functions
  of the present tense."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit allows pupils to explore and express their identity in the
  context of revisiting present tense weak verbs, singular and plural nouns and gender neutral
  language. Pupils explore this in the context of their own nationality, identity and
  lifestyles. Cultural enrichment and practice on large numbers and translation into English
  provided through a focus on Switzerland and then Germany (Bavaria), the Oktoberfest, and some
  lesser known places and a dialect spoken in northern Germany.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2939-6 ;
  curric:id "2939"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.641190Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-verb-to-be-being ,
    oakcurric:thread-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-2948
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: Das Schulleben"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-das-schulleben" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits separable verbs in present and perfect tenses, adjective
  agreement and use of time, manner, place adverbs. It introduces nouns and adjectives with
  prepositions, the preposition and adverb 'bis', superlative prenominal adjectives and
  abstract nouns, for example 'das Gute'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate a wide range of grammar including present
  and perfect tenses, word order, and adjective agreement as prenominal superlative adjectives
  are introduced. Opportunities for comprehension and extended spoken production are provided
  in the context of the German education system. Pupils compare school life this year and last
  year, read about therapy dogs, peer pressure, and deepen their knowledge of the German school
  system in normal and unusual settings.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2948-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2948-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2948-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2948-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2948-5 ;
  curric:id "2948"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.657263Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-3526
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: Reiseziele"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-reiseziele" ;
  rdfs:comment """This consolidation unit revisits all of the grammar covered in previous units in
  the context of travel destinations in Germany, Austria and Switzerland. Pupils learn to
  use 'man' in order to avoid the passive, and also learn 'sein' and 'ihr' in nominative,
  accusative and dative to mean 'its'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils explore the grammar covered in previous units in a
  rich cultural context of towns and regions in Germany and Austria, their history, traditions,
  renowned infrastructure and famous events. . The grammar is revisited in these contexts along
  with known and new vocabulary, allowing the pupils to consolidate and extend their
  comprehension and their production skills.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-8 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-9 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3526-10 ;
  curric:id "3526"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.661046Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
