oakcurric:unit-2955
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: meine Welt"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-meine-welt" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits a range of known grammar in the context of social and global
  inequalities. The future and conditional tenses are reactivated. 'Nach' and 'nachdem',
  'vor' and 'bevor' are revisited. Word order 3 with conjunctions ob, sobald, solange, bis
  and damit are practised."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils apply known grammar with known and new vocabulary in
  the context of global inequalities and environmental challenges. Most prepositions and
  conjunctions are revisited, along with consolidation of the future and conditional tenses and
  question formation using wo-compound questions words, for example wobei, woran. Pupils learn
  about loneliness, poverty and mental health in Germany, the German energy crisis and
  rewilding . Pupils practise all this in listening and responding to longer passages, extended
  spoken production and asking and answering spoken questions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2955-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2955-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2955-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2955-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2955-5 ;
  curric:id "2955"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.872826Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
