oakcurric:unit-2954
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: Kulturszene"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-kulturszene" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits previously taught grammar with practice of the perfect tense
  (haben and sein) and simple past with früher, gern and lieber. Comparative adverb
  structures are consolidated along with plural nouns and irregular nationality nouns. 'wo'
  and 'was' in relative clauses are revisited."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit provides a cultural backdrop in which pupils revisit known
  grammar and vocabulary, adding new vocabulary as they explore cultural traditions and famous
  lives in German speaking countries. The perfect tense with haben and sein and the simple past
  are reactivated, together with comparative adverbs, plural nouns, nationality nouns and
  relative clauses. Cultural traditions in Austria and Switzerland are explored in texts and
  exercises, and the lives and influence of famous German speakers, including the Grimm
  Brothers and the first Nobel peace prize winner Bertha Suttner are examined.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2954-6 ;
  curric:id "2954"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.582200Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
