oakcurric:unit-2950
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Media and technology: Technologie"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-technologie" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits present and future tenses and modal verbs and consolidates
  knowledge of verb-subject questions in single and two-verb structures. It introduces the
  imperative (informal - du/ihr) of weak verbs and the Da-Wo compounds 'worum' and 'darum'
  as pupils explore online communication."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils consolidate their knowledge of the present tense to
  describe simple and ongoing activities. They reinforce their knowledge of modal verbs and two
  verb structures in statements and questions and extend this with the imperative in the 'du'
  and 'ihr' forms. Pupils apply this in writing emails and in social media messages, and in
  discussions on sport.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2950-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2950-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2950-3 ;
  curric:id "2950"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.733659Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
