oakcurric:unit-2945
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: Beziehungen und Feste"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-beziehungen-und-feste" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits verbs with prepositions, and adds to previous knowledge of da-
  and wo- compounds in the accusative and the dative. Reflexive verbs are revisited in the
  context of family relationships, together with word order and the use of wen, wem, with
  reflexive questions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit on everyday culture revisits and extends known grammar in new
  contexts of family relationships and festivals and traditions. Da- and wo-compounds are
  revisited and extended in use with verbs plus a range of prepositions. Direct and indirect
  object pronouns are also revisited, along with reflexive verbs in both statement and question
  form. The rich context includes examples of women as role models in motor sport, an article
  on young carers and Karneval in Germany. Vocabulary is extended with a rich text on world
  religions celebrated in Germany.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2945-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2945-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2945-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2945-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2945-5 ;
  curric:id "2945"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.738438Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages .

oakcurric:unit-2957
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: Wiederholung: mein Leben, meine Zukunft"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-mein-leben-meine-zukunft" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit begins formal revision of the course, with known grammar and vocabulary
  reactivated throughout. Pupils apply knowledge on plural nouns, present and perfect
  tenses, including reflexive and separable verbs, imperfect tense, modals, verbs with
  prepositions, future tense and 'möcht-'"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils revise previous grammar and vocabulary knowledge in
  the context of their current lives as teenagers, an impression of the future at university,
  and a cultural visit to Salzburg. As pupils' knowledge has progressed, this unit draws
  together past, present tenses, including reflexive and separable verbs. Pupils also apply the
  future tense, including present tense with future meaning..They practise applying more
  complex language, including verbs, nouns and adjectives with preposition with greater
  confidence and fluency,""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2957-6 ;
  curric:id "2957"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.717449Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order .

oakcurric:unit-3843
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Lifestyle and wellbeing: Wiederholung: Gesundheit"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-wiederholung-gesundheit" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit continues to revisit known grammar and vocabulary from the entire
  course, with a focus on developing skills of role-play, conversation and reading."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils reactivate their grammar and vocabulary knowledge
  within the context of healthy living This unit will help pupils to develop their confidence
  in being able to apply their knowledge in comprehension and in asking and answering questions
  and role play practice in these new contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3843-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3843-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3843-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3843-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3843-5 ;
  curric:id "3843"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.769173Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3523
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: positive Lebensentscheidungen"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-positive-lebensentscheidungen" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revises word patterns, plurals, direct and indirect object pronouns and
  interrogative and demonstrative adjectives (welch-) and (jed-). Nominative and accusative
  use of abstract adjectival neuter nouns after viel and wenig are taught in the context of
  healthy living and lifestyle choices."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In the context of positive lifestyle choices this unit revisits a broad
  range of previously taught grammar on word patterns, plurals, adjectives, present and
  conditional tenses. Pupils expand their vocabulary in reading and responding to texts and
  discussing lifestyle options, for example veganism. They learn to use adjectival neuter nouns
  in describing a healthy lifestyle. Later, they explore numbers and interrogative adjectives
  in the context of shopping, with cultural input on a famous Berlin department store and the
  initiatives of a famous German 'zero waste shopping' pioneer.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3523-8 ;
  curric:id "3523"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.917324Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts .

oakcurric:unit-3522
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: Zukunftsentscheidungen"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-zukunftsentscheidungen" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits present tense modal verbs. It consolidates the nominalisation
  of infinitives, feminine word formation (ending in -ung) and 'um...zu' and 'statt...zu'
  clauses. Pupils also learn 'ohne....zu' and phrases for expressing options, including
  'entweder....oder' and 'weder...noch'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit revisits knowledge of the present tense and word patterns for
  feminine nouns in the context of future study plans. Pupils apply new learning of the phrases
  'ohne...zu', 'entweder...noch' 'weder...noch' in discussing the options of the Abitur or
  professional training. Nominalisation of nouns is revised as pupils explore future decisions,
  and pupils apply their knowledge of modal verbs in extended speaking on what they want to
  learn for their future.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3522-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3522-2 ;
  curric:id "3522"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.963290Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns .

oakcurric:unit-2959
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and Tourism: Wiederholung: Menschen und Orte"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-menschen-und-orte" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit continues the focus on known grammar and vocabulary, with a spotlight on
  negation, adjective agreement, compound nouns, word pattern rules and read aloud practice
  of sound-symbol correspondences."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils reactivate their grammar and vocabulary knowledge
  within the context of geographical and cultural knowledge about North and South Germany. and
  about healthy lifestyles. This unit will help pupils to develop their confidence in being
  able to apply their knowledge in comprehension and in asking and answering questions and role
  play practice in these new contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2959-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2959-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2959-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2959-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2959-5 ;
  curric:id "2959"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.283997Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-negation ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives .

oakcurric:unit-3527
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My World: Wiederholung: Einflüsse und Ereignisse"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-beruhmte-deutschsprachige" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit consolidates revision of vocabulary and grammar with a focus on word
  order 1, word order 2 (inversion) and word order 3 with subordinating conjunctions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit allows pupils to apply their vocabulary and grammar knowledge in
  order to learn about the lives of famous German speakers. Most elements of word order are
  revisited as pupils build greater confidence in applying these rules more accurately.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3527-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3527-2 ;
  curric:id "3527"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.289977Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

