  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.064425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26575
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can create adjectives from nouns and use the pronoun 'man' to express what 'is
  done' and 'was done' by people in general."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.064600Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26566
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use a range of present tense verbs, including those with small changes to the
  stem, in extended writing about living with a disability."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.064604Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26474
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use word order 2 and form questions in the perfect tense in the context of
  interesting past experiences."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.064795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26496
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use a range of present tense verbs, including those with small changes to the
  stem, to discuss sport and free-time pursuits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.064903Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26437
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use the perfect tense with 'haben' and irregular past participles in the
  context of the experiences of Syrians in Germany."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065261Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26429
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use present tense weak verbs, 'nicht' and 'kein' to talk about learning a
  language."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26483
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can form and use superlative adjectives and adverbs when discussing topics in a
  school context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065390Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26606
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can confidently complete a role-play, photo description and follow-up conversation
  in the style of the speaking exam."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065478Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26525
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use dates, years and numbers correctly and infer the meaning of unknown words
  when reading about and planning a trip across Europe."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065510Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26546
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can create formal and informal questions in the context of helping the
  environment."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065679Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26536
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can confidently use a range of verbs in the perfect and imperfect tenses, and
  apply this knowledge to listening, reading, and translation tasks with a historical
  context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26436
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can plan, select language, and check for accuracy to write an extended text in
  German about an interesting person."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26471
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label "I can use modal verbs in the imperfect tense to talk about work and studying."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.065800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26570
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use the future tense and conditional, applying the 2-verb rule when discussing
  the energy crisis in Germany and possible solutions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26441
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can form yes/no questions in the perfect and imperfect tenses to ask questions
  about famous German speakers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066192Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26462
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label "I can use 'werden' with the infinitive to discuss my future plans."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066334Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26481
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can add agreements to adjectives to provide details when talking about the German
  school system."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066383Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26528
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I understand the format and use of cardinal and ordinal numbers in German, and can
  use the correct preposition to express 'to'."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066387Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26447
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label "I can use the correct word order when giving my opinion about photos."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.066702Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26554
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can apply a checklist of knowledge to support my use of the perfect and imperfect
  tenses, and can apply this when reading and writing in German."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.067049Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26557
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can understand and read aloud vocabulary relating to human rights and can ask
  questions using 'wer', 'wen' and 'wem' when discussing rights for disabled people."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.067349Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26592
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can transcribe and understand German speakers talking in a range of contexts about
  technology."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.067719Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26558
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use adverbs to give and respond to detailed responses in the past tense, form
  past participles of a range of weak verbs, and apply this knowledge when translating into
  German."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.067814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26515
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use a range of prepositional verbs, 'da-' and 'wo-' compounds and new
  vocabulary in the context of the digital world and favourite online influencers."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068180Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26461
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label "I can use 'wenn' to describe outcomes of actions."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068824Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26460
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use 'können' and 'dürfen' to describe what people are able to do and what
  people are allowed to do."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068828Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26492
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can recognise and use the imperative of weak verbs to give instructions or advice
  in the context of technology."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068886Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26453
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use dative verbs, indirect object pronouns, and dative prepositions to discuss
  people and activities in the context of festivals."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068898Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26469
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can tell the time and use 'es' in different contexts, making meaning more concise
  when discussing life for young Germans."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:30:41.068910Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:pupillessonoutcome-lesson-26564
  a curric:PupilLessonOutcome ;
  rdfs:label """I can use prepositions ‘vor’ and ‘nach’ and conjunctions ‘bevor’ and ‘nachdem’ in
